'''''Underwater Dreams''''' is a [[documentary film]] written, directed, and produced by [[Mary Mazzio|Mary Marzio]]. The film chronicles the story of how the sons of undocumented [[Mexican people|Mexican]] immigrants learned how to build underwater robots, and go up against [[MIT]] in the process.

==Synopsis==
''Underwater Dreams'' is the true story of a team of undocumented Mexican high school students, who under the tutelage of two of their teachers, enter the  Marine Advanced Technology Education (MATE) Center's annual [[Robot competition#Marine Advanced Technology Education Center Competition|International ROV competition]],<ref>{{cite web|title=Marine Advanced Technology Education Center|url=http://marinetech.org|accessdate=30 July 2014}}</ref> which is sponsored by the [[National Science Foundation]], [[Marine Technology Society]], [[Office of Ocean Exploration|NOAA Office of Ocean Exploration]] and [[NASA]]. The four boys from [[Carl Hayden High School]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Falcon Robotics FRC Team 842|url=https://sites.google.com/site/falconroboticsfrcteam842/home|publisher=Google Sites|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref>{{dead|date=May 2019}}  in [[Phoenix, Arizona|Phoenix]] competed against college teams all across the United States including [[MIT]].<ref>{{cite web|title=About the Film|url=http://www.underwaterdreamsfilm.com/about-the-film/|publisher=www.underwaterdreamsfilm.com|accessdate=29 April 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Underwater Dreams: A Reel Progress screening and live Q&A|url=http://www.americanprogress.org/events/2014/04/22/88434/underwater-dreams/|accessdate=29 April 2014|newspaper=AmericanProgress.org|date=29 April 2014}}</ref>

Another film, ''[[Spare Parts (2015 film)|Spare Parts]]'' about the Carl Hayden team was released January 16, 2015.  It stars [[George Lopez]] and [[Marisa Tomei]].<ref name=mit>{{cite news|last=Brinkman|first=Camilla|title=Underwater Dreams Features MIT ROV Team|url=https://alum.mit.edu/pages/sliceofmit/2014/03/17/underwater-dreams-features-mit-rov-team/|accessdate=29 April 2014|newspaper=Slice of MIT|date=17 March 2014}}</ref>

